1. File and Directory Operations
ls → List files in a directory
pwd → Print working directory
cd <directory> → Change directory
mkdir <directory> → Create a new directory
rmdir <directory> → Remove an empty directory
rm <file> → Remove a file
cp <source> <destination> → Copy files
mv <source> <destination> → Move or rename files


2. File Content Operations
cat <file> → Display file content
tac <file> → Display file content in reverse
more <file> → View file content page by page
less <file> → View file with navigation
head -n <number> <file> → Show first N lines
tail -n <number> <file> → Show last N lines
grep "pattern" <file> → Search for a pattern in a file


3. Permissions and Ownership
chmod 755 <file> → Change file permissions
chown user:group <file> → Change file owner
ls -l → List files with permissions


4. Process Management
ps → View running processes
top → Display real-time process info
kill <PID> → Terminate a process by PID
killall <process_name> → Kill all processes by name


5. Networking
ping <host> → Check connectivity
netstat -tulnp → List open ports
curl <URL> → Fetch web content
wget <URL> → Download a file


6. Text Processing
awk '{print $1}' <file> → Extract specific columns
sed 's/old/new/g' <file> → Replace text in a file
cut -d':' -f1 <file> → Cut fields from a file
sort <file> → Sort lines in a file
uniq <file> → Remove duplicate lines


7. Compression & Archiving
tar -cvf archive.tar <files> → Create an archive
tar -xvf archive.tar → Extract an archive
zip file.zip <files> → Create a ZIP file
unzip file.zip → Extract a ZIP file


8. System Information
df -h → Disk space usage
du -sh <directory> → Directory size
free -m → Check RAM usage
uptime → System uptime
whoami → Current user
hostname → System hostname


9. Shell Scripting Basics
#!/bin/bash → Define script interpreter
echo "Hello, World!" → Print message
read var → Read user input
if [ condition ]; then ... fi → Conditional statements
for var in {1..5}; do ... done → Loops
while [ condition ]; do ... done → While loop
